    {
      "question": "An architect is designing a rectangular community garden. The length of the garden is $3$ m more than twice its breadth. The area of the garden is $119$ m$^2$. Let the breadth of the garden be $x$ m. Based on this information, answer the following questions.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "Which of the following quadratic equations represents the area of the garden?",
          "answer": "(C)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$",
            "(B) $x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$",
            "(C) $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$",
            "(D) $2x^2 - 3x + 119 = 0$"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the roots of the quadratic equation $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$ using the factorisation method.",
          "answer": "$x = 7$ or $x = -17/2$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Set the equation $2x^2 + 3x - 119 = 0$.",
              "Find two numbers whose product is $2 \times (-119) = -238$ and sum is $3$.",
              "The numbers are $17$ and $-14$.",
              "Rewrite as $2x^2 + 17x - 14x - 119 = 0$.",
              "Factorise to get $x(2x + 17) - 7(2x + 17) = 0$.",
              "Solve $(x - 7)(2x + 17) = 0$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$2x^2 + 17x - 14x - 119 = 0 \\\\ x(2x + 17) - 7(2x + 17) = 0 \\\\ (x - 7)(2x + 17) = 0 \\\\ x = 7, x = -17/2$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "What is the breadth of the garden in metres?",
          "answer": "$7$ m",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "From the previous part, the roots are $7$ and $-8.5$.",
              "Since the breadth cannot be negative, we reject $-8.5$.",
              "Therefore, the breadth is $7$ m."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "What is the length of the garden in metres?",
          "answer": "$17$ m",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "The length is given by $2x + 3$.",
              "Substitute $x = 7$.",
              "Length = $2(7) + 3 = 14 + 3 = 17$ m."
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
